     (South Africa);
   • The Cybercrimes Act 19 of 2020 (South Africa);
   • Applicable international copyright treaties including the Berne
     Convention and the WIPO Copyright Treaty.

   In the event of infringement, the Company reserves the right to pursue, at
   its sole discretion and without prior notice:

   (a) an urgent interdict (injunction) without notice to restrain ongoing
       or threatened infringement;

   (b) a claim for actual damages, including loss of profits and reputational
       harm;

   (c) a claim for statutory or additional damages to the maximum extent
       permitted by applicable law;

   (d) an account of profits derived from the infringing activity;

   (e) costs of litigation, including attorney and own-client costs; and

   (f) referral to law enforcement authorities where the conduct constitutes
       a criminal offence.

   The Company may elect to enforce its rights internationally in any
   jurisdiction in which infringing activity occurs or has effect.

